DevModel.EngineeringDescription: This is the FDM for iCOM SC (chillers) SW family

LocalStringDefinitions.String: The general classification for this system
Compressor Shut Down - Ambient Air Low Temp Limit
When the temperature of ambient air falls below this lower threshold, the compressor will be shut off. Correct condensing pressure cannot be achieved when temperature is too low.
For water cooled condensers, the temperature of the water entering the heat exchanger, before cooling the refrigerant.
For water cooled condensers, the temperature of the water exiting the heat exchanger, after cooling the refrigerant.
Identification of the pump that is currently running.
Present adiabatic cooling utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum.
Present compressor economizer utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum.
Present free cooling utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum.
Fluid temperature measured at the outlet of the unit.
Water Filter Differential Pressure Over Threshold
The differential pressure across the water filter has exceeded an upper threshold, indicating a dirty filter.
Compressor has returned to normal load capacity.
Compressor has returned to normal load capacity.
Compressor has returned to normal load capacity.
Master Unit Input Power Out of Range
Master unit input power parameters are not within the expected operational range.
Sub-Unit Input Power Out of Range
Sub-unit input power parameters are not within the expected operational range.
Master Unit Shutdown - Input Power Issues
Master unit has been shut down due to excessive input power out of range conditions.
Sub-unit has been shut down due to excessive input power out of range conditions.
Unit has been shut down due to excessive input power out of range conditions.
Compressor contactor is not closing during compressor startup or is not opening during compressor shutdown.
Two or more sub-units are defined, but only one is allowed.
Condenser Max Fan Speed Override Reset
Fan has returned to normal operating speed.
Free memory has dropped below a critical threshold.
Evaporator Return Fluid Over Temp Warning Threshold
Warning threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Over Temp] event.
Evaporator Return Fluid Over Temp Alarm Threshold
Alarm threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Over Temp] event.
Evaporator Return Fluid Under Temp Warning Threshold
Warning threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Under Temp] event.
Evaporator Return Fluid Under Temp Alarm Threshold
Alarm threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Under Temp] event.
[Evaporator Return Fluid Temperature] has exceeded a threshold. The event is deactivated when the temperature drops below the threshold.
[Evaporator Return Fluid Temperature] has dropped below a threshold. The event is deactivated when the temperature rises above the threshold.
Compressor capacity control state. When 'ON', the cooling capacity of the compressor has been reduced.
Threshold value used in the [Compressor Hours Exceeded] event.
Compressor is shut down due to high head pressure.
Compressor is shut down due to low suction pressure.
Compressor is shut down due to thermal overload.
Compressor head pressure has exceeded an upper threshold.
Compressor is shut down due to low differential pressure.
Condenser fan speed expressed as a percentage of the maximum rated speed.
Condenser fan is not operating within its operational parameters.
Refrigerant pressure in condenser coil is too low.
Fluid pressure. This is the pressure within a closed water/glycol circuit.
[Fluid Pressure] has dropped below a specified threshold.
Compressor commanded to stop, but continues to run.
Operating hours for pump since last reset of this value.
Threshold value used in the [Pump Hours Exceeded] event.
System is shut down due to loss of flow in all available pumps.
Loss of flow is detected in pump 1. This condition occurs when no flow is detected through the flow switch.
Loss of flow is detected in pump 2. This condition occurs when no flow is detected through the flow switch.
Temperature control band above [Actual Supply Fluid Temp Set Point]. If [Return Fluid Temperature] is within this band, fluid cooling operations are proportionally controlled.
Actual Supply Fluid Temp Set Point
The actual set point value being used for the desired fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit.
Set point 1 of desired fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit.
Set point 2 of desired fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit.
Supply Fluid Over Temp Warning Threshold
Threshold value used to generate a [Supply Fluid Over Temp] warning.
Second threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Over Temp] event.
Threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Under Temp] event.
Second threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Under Temp] event.
[Supply Fluid Temperature] has exceeded a specified threshold.
Fluid temperature measured at the inlet of the unit.
Threshold value used in the [Return Fluid Over Temp] event.
Second threshold value used in the [Return Fluid Over Temp] event.
Threshold value used in the [Return Fluid Under Temp] event.
Second threshold value used in the [Return Fluid Under Temp] event.
[Return Fluid Temperature] has exceeded a specified threshold.
[Return Fluid Temperature] has dropped below a specified threshold.
The return fluid temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range.
Teamwork Return Fluid Temp Sensor Issue
The return fluid temperature sensors for all Teamwork units are disconnected or the signals are out of range.
Minimum temperature delta required between return fluid and external ambient air temperatures in order to enable free cooling.
Threshold value used in the [Free Cooling Valve Hours Exceeded] event.
Operating hours for free cooling valve since last reset of this value.
[Free Cooling Valve Hours] has exceeded [Free Cooling Valve Hours Threshold].
The ambient air temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range.
Fluid temperature measured at the inlet of the evaporator.
The evaporator inlet temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range.
Teamwork Evaporator Inlet Temp Sensor Issue
The evaporator inlet temperature sensors for all Teamwork units are disconnected or the signals are out of range.
Evaporator outlet fluid temperature has dropped below the freeze threshold. Evaporator has been shut down, but will restart when the temperature rises above the threshold.
Evaporator Fluid Freeze - Manual Reset Required
Evaporator outlet fluid temperature has dropped below the freeze threshold. Evaporator has been shut down and requires a manual reset.
Desired brine fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit.
Supply Heated Water Temp Set Point
Desired heated water temperature at the outlet of the unit.
Subgroup Event Occurred During Communication Loss
While subgroup unit communication was lost, an event occurred on the subgroup unit. Please check subgroup unit event log.
The master has lost communication with subgroup unit.
The frequency with which control operations rotate from the current lead unit to a standby unit.
The hour at which control operations shift from the lead unit to the standby unit on the interval selected in [Standby Unit Rotation Frequency].
The minute of [Standby Unit Rotation Hour] at which control operations shift from the lead unit to the standby unit on the interval selected in [Standby Unit Rotation Frequency].
Operating hours for compressor since last reset of this value.
Compressor High Head Pressure - Event Control

Enable/disable the activation of the [Compressor High Head Pressure] event. If set to 'disabled', the event will not be annunciated. This implies that the event will not be placed in any active event list or in any event history list.
Compressor High Head Pressure - Event Type
The event type for the [Compressor High Head Pressure] event.
Compressor Low Suction Pressure - Event Control

Enable/disable the activation of the [Compressor Low Suction Pressure] event. If set to 'disabled', the event will not be annunciated. This implies that the event will not be placed in any active event list or in any event history list.
Compressor Low Suction Pressure - Event Type
The event type for the [Compressor Low Suction Pressure] event.

Enable/disable the activation of the [Compressor Thermal Overload] event. If set to 'disabled', the event will not be annunciated. This implies that the event will not be placed in any active event list or in any event history list.
The event type for the [Compressor Thermal Overload] event.
Supply Fluid Over Temp Alarm Threshold
Threshold value used to generate a [Supply Fluid Over Temp] alarm.
Supply Fluid Under Temp Warning Threshold
Threshold value used to generate a [Supply Fluid Under Temp] warning.
Threshold value used to generate a [Supply Fluid Under Temp] alarm.
Supply Fluid Under Temp Alarm Threshold
Return Fluid Over Temp Warning Threshold
Return Fluid Over Temp Alarm Threshold
Threshold value used to generate a [Return Fluid Over Temp] warning.
Threshold value used to generate a [Return Fluid Over Temp] alarm.
Return Fluid Under Temp Warning Threshold
Return Fluid Under Temp Alarm Threshold
Threshold value used to generate a [Return Fluid Under Temp] warning.
Threshold value used to generate a [Return Fluid Under Temp] alarm.

DataEnum.EngineeringDescription: The general classification for this device.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription: When the temperature of ambient air falls below this lower threshold, the compressor will be shut off. Correct condensing pressure cannot be achieved when temperature is too low.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription: Compressor commanded to stop, but continues to run. Event is deactivated by manual reset.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Hierarchical value for SNMP and Modbus indexing of multi-module data points.

DataEnum.EngineeringDescription:
Compressor capacity control state. When 'ON', the cooling capacity of the compressor has been reduced.
iCOM Specific: When 'ON', control decisions based on operational measurements, such as head pressure, can reduce or increase the compressor capacity from its requested cooling capacity.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Compressor head pressure.
Operating hours for compressor since last reset of this value. iCOM Specific: The only valid writable value is zero.
Threshold value used in the [Compressor Hours Exceeded] event. See evt_comp_hrsExceeded.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
[Compressor Hours] has exceeded [Compressor Hours Threshold]. Event threshold is specified in val_comp_tm_opThreshold. Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_comp_tm_op.
iCOM Specific: This event will deactivate when val_comp_tm_op is manually reset to zero.

Compressor is shut down due to high head pressure. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_comp_prsHighEnable st_comp_prsHighType
iCOM Specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible.

Compressor is shut down due to low suction pressure. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_comp_prsLowEnable st_comp_prsLowType
iCOM Specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible.

Compressor is shut down due to thermal overload. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_comp_thermOverloadEnable st_comp_thermOverloadType
iCOM Specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible.
Compressor low oil pressure. The event is deactivated by manual reset. This is the lubricant oil inside the crankcase of the compressor.
Compressor is shut down due to low differential pressure. The event is deactivated by manual reset.

Compressor capacity has been reduced. This may be caused by, but is not limited to: an external input signal, safety considerations, or system algorithmic control. The event is deactivated when full capacity is restored.
Compressor has returned to normal load capacity.
Compressor contactor is not closing during compressor startup or is not opening during compressor shutdown.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Hierarchical value for SNMP and Modbus indexing of multi-module data points.
Condenser fan speed expressed as a percentage of the maximum rated speed.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription: Condenser fan is not operating within its operational parameters. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
Refrigerant pressure in condenser coil is too low. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
Fan speed exceeding the maximum set point in order to alleviate a high temperature or pressure condition.
Fan has returned to normal operating speed.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription:
Fluid pressure. This is the pressure within a closed water/glycol circuit.
iCOM: This value is always measured, regardless of whether a pump is operating.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
[Fluid Pressure] has dropped below a specified threshold. The event is deactivated when the pressure rises above the threshold.
Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_clng_prs_fluid.

The return fluid temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range. The event is deactivated when sensor signal is re-established.
iCOM specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription:
Temperature control band above [Actual Supply Fluid Temp Set Point]. If [Return Fluid Temperature] is within this band, fluid cooling operations are proportionally controlled.
Example: [Actual Supply Fluid Temp Set Point] is set to 40 degrees. [Fluid Cooling Proportional Band] is set to 10 degrees. When [Return Fluid Temperature] is between 40 and 50 degrees, the unit will perform proportional cooling operations on the fluid.
iCOM Specific: The return fluid is returned TO this unit to be cooled and then supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

ReportDescriptor.EngineeringDescription: Data points related to the supply fluid, also referred to as the outlet fluid.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription: Set point 1 of desired fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit. iCOM Specific: See val_clng_tmp_supFluSetPtActual.
Set point 2 of desired fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit. iCOM Specific: See val_clng_tmp_supFluSetPtActual.

Second threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Over Temp] event. See event evt_clng_tmpSupFluOver.
This threshold is for a more severe condition than the threshold defined by val_clng_tmp_supFluOverThrshld.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

Threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Over Temp] event. See event evt_clng_tmpSupFluOver. See also val_clng_tmp_supFluOverThrshld2.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

Threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Under Temp] event. See event evt_clng_tmpSupFluUnder. See also val_clng_tmp_supFluUnderThrshld2.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

Second threshold value used in the [Supply Fluid Under Temp] event. See event evt_clng_tmpSupFluUnder.
This threshold is for a more severe condition than the threshold defined by val_clng_tmp_supFluUnderThrshld.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
[Supply Fluid Temperature] has exceeded [Supply Fluid Over Temp Threshold]. The event is deactivated when the temperature drops below the threshold.
Event threshold is specified in val_clng_tmp_supFluOverThrshld. Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_clng_tmp_supFlu.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_clng_tmpSupFluOverEnable st_clng_tmpSupFluOverType
iCOM specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

[Supply Fluid Temperature] has dropped below a specified threshold. The event is deactivated when the temperature rises above the threshold.
Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_clng_tmp_supFlu.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_clng_tmpSupFluUnderEnable st_clng_tmpSupFluUnderType
iCOM specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event threshold is internally specified and is not accessible. This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

The supply fluid temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range. The event is deactivated when sensor signal is re-established.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_clng_snsrSupFluIssueEnable st_clng_snsrSupFluIssueType
iCOM specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible. This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.
System is shut down due to loss of flow in all available pumps. Event is deactivated by manual reset.

Loss of flow is detected in pump 1. The loss of flow condition occurs when no differential pressure is detected across the pump. The event is deactivated when flow is re-established.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_pump_flowLossEnable1 st_pump_flowLossType1
iCOM specific: Event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible.

Loss of flow is detected in pump 2. The loss of flow condition occurs when no differential pressure is detected across the pump. The event is deactivated when flow is re-established.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_pump_flowLossEnable2 st_pump_flowLossType2
iCOM specific: Event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible.

ReportDescriptor.EngineeringDescription: Data points that describe each pump in the system.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Hierarchical value for SNMP and Modbus indexing of multi-module data points.
Operating hours for pump since last reset of this value. iCOM Specific: The only valid writable value is zero.
Threshold value used in the [Pump Hours Exceeded] event. See evt_pump_hrsExceeded.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
[Pump Hours] has exceeded [Pump Hours Threshold]. Event threshold is specified in val_pump_tm_opThreshold. Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_pump_tm_op.
iCOM Specific: This event will deactivate when val_pump_tm_op is manually reset to zero.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription:
Minimum temperature delta required between return fluid and external ambient air temperatures in order to enable free cooling.
Example: [Return Fluid Temperature] is 60 degrees. [Free Cooling Temperature Delta] is set to 6 degrees. If external ambient air temperature is below 54 degrees, free cooling may be enabled.
See val_clng_tmp_retFlu.
iCOM Specific: The return fluid is returned TO this unit to be cooled.
Free cooling valve open position. 0% = fully closed, 100% = fully open.
Operating hours for free cooling valve since last reset of this value. iCOM Specific: The only valid writable value is zero.
Threshold value used in the [Free Cooling Valve Hours Exceeded] event. See evt_valv_hrsExceededFC.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
[Free Cooling Valve Hours] has exceeded [Free Cooling Valve Hours Threshold]. Event threshold is specified in val_valv_tm_opThresholdFC. Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_valv_tm_opFC.
iCOM Specific: This event will deactivate when val_valv_tm_opFC is manually reset to zero.

The external air sensor A is disconnected or the signal is out of range. The event is deactivated when sensor signal is re-established.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_ext_snsrAirIssueEnableA st_ext_snsrAirIssueTypeA
iCOM specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription: Fluid temperature measured at the inlet of the evaporator.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription: The evaporator inlet temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range. The event is deactivated when sensor signal is re-established.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription:
Alarm threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Over Temp] event. See event evt_evap_tmpRetFluOver.
This threshold is for a more severe condition than the threshold defined by val_evap_tmp_retFluOverThrshWarn.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

Warning threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Over Temp] event. See event evt_evap_tmpRetFluOver. See also val_evap_tmp_retFluOverThrshAlrm.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

Warning threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Under Temp] event. See event evt_evap_tmpRetFluUnder. See also val_evap_tmp_retFluUnderThrshAlrm.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

Alarm threshold value used in the [Evaporator Return Fluid Under Temp] event. See event evt_evap_tmpRetFluUnder.
This threshold is for a more severe condition than the threshold defined by val_evap_tmp_retFluUnderThrshWarn.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
[Evaporator Return Fluid Temperature] has exceeded a threshold. The event is deactivated when the temperature drops below the threshold.
Event threshold is specified in val_evap_tmp_retFluOverThrshWarn and val_evap_tmp_retFluOverThrshAlrm. Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_ evap_tmp_retFlu.
iCOM specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

[Evaporator Return Fluid Temperature] has dropped below a threshold. The event is deactivated when the temperature rises above the threshold.
Event threshold is specified in val_evap_tmp_retFluUnderThrshWarn and val_evap_tmp_retFluUnderThrshAlrm. Value used in comparison against threshold is specified in val_evap_tmp_retFlu.
iCOM specific: This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Hierarchical value for SNMP and Modbus indexing of multi-module data points.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription: Evaporator outlet fluid temperature has dropped below the freeze threshold. Evaporator has been shut down, but will restart when the temperature rises above the threshold.
Evaporator outlet fluid temperature has dropped below the freeze threshold. Evaporator has been shut down and requires a manual reset.

The supply refrigerant temperature sensor is disconnected or the signal is out of range. The event is deactivated when sensor signal is re-established.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_clng_snsrSupRfgIssueEnable st_clng_snsrSupRfgIssueType
iCOM specific: The event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period. Event delay is internally controlled and is not accessible. This is the refrigerant being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription:
Desired brine fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit.
iCOM Specific: This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations. Brine is only used on units that have the necessary mechanical components to operate at extremely low temperatures.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription:
The number of standby units.
iCOM Specific: A standby unit will become active if the lead unit has been shut down due to a critical event. A standby unit is also used in a rotational setup.

DataEnum.EngineeringDescription: The frequency with which control operations rotate from the current lead unit to a standby unit.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: The hour at which control operations shift from the lead unit to the standby unit on the interval selected in [Standby Unit Rotation Frequency]. Used in conjunction with val_sys_tm_standbyRotateMin and st_sys_standbyRotateFreq.

The minute of [Standby Unit Rotation Hour] at which control operations shift from the lead unit to the standby unit on the interval selected in [Standby Unit Rotation Frequency]. Used in conjunction with val_sys_tm_standbyRotateHr and st_sys_standbyRotateFreq.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription:
The external input contact 1. It is either active or inactive.
It becomes inactive when the external signal is not active.

The external input contact 2. It is either active or inactive.
It becomes inactive when the external signal is not active.

Unit was turned on.
iCOM Specific: This is a notification event and doesn't require deactivation. See st_sys_operatingReason.

Unit was turned off.
iCOM Specific: This is a notification event and doesn't require deactivation. See st_sys_operatingReason.

Communication with master unit has been lost. The event is deactivated when communication is re-established.
The behavior of this event may optionally be modified by: st_sys_masterCommLostEnable st_sys_masterCommLostType
iCOM specific: Event will not be activated unless it is enabled and the event condition is true for the full event delay period.

While subgroup unit communication was lost, an event occurred on the subgroup unit. Please check subgroup unit event log.
The evt_sys_subgroupEvtWhileCommLoss event is deactivated by manual reset.
Humidifier control board is required to be connected, but no signal is detected. The event is deactivated when signal is detected.
The differential pressure across the water filter has exceeded an upper threshold, indicating a dirty filter. The event is deactivated when the pressure is below the threshold.

Master unit input power parameters are not within the expected operational range. These parameters include, but are not limited to, voltage, phase rotation, and phase angle. The event is deactivated when the parameters return to normal operating range.
iCOMSpecific: This will cause shutdown of compressors and pumps.

Sub-unit input power parameters are not within the expected operational range. These parameters include, but are not limited to, voltage, phase rotation, and phase angle. The event is deactivated when the parameters return to normal operating range.
iCOMSpecific: This will cause shutdown of compressors and pumps.
Unit has been shut down due to excessive input power out of range conditions. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
Master unit has been shut down due to excessive input power out of range conditions. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
Sub-unit has been shut down due to excessive input power out of range conditions. The event is deactivated by manual reset.
Two or more sub-units are defined, but only one is allowed.
RAM or RAM backup battery is not operating correctly. The event is deactivated when operation returns to normal.
Free memory has dropped below a critical threshold. The event is deactivated when free memory is no longer below the threshold.
Unit code has not been entered and saved. iCOM Specific: The unit code defines the specific options contained within an iCOM unit.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Hierarchical value for SNMP and Modbus indexing of multi-module data points.

DataEvent16.EngineeringDescription: The master has lost communication with subgroup unit. The event is deactivated when communication is re-established.

DataEnum.EngineeringDescription:
The operating status for the system. The intent of this data definition is to provide a high level status of the system. The valid states are: Normal Operation, StartUp, Normal with Warning, Normal with Alarm, and Abnormal Operation.
For a more detailed explanation of this data definition, see the Engineering Reference Document.

DataText.EngineeringDescription:
System model identifier. This is the marketing model identifier that is meant for display purposes / human consumption.
Do not use this field for determining programmatic behavior.
End user assigned name for the system. The name allows users to easily recognize the system.

DataEnum.EngineeringDescription: Current operating state of the system. Allowable states: Off - The unit is not providing services and will not provide services in this state. On - The unit is able to provide services as needed. Standby - The unit is not currently providing services, but can do so by transitioning into the 'on' state.
System control mode. Allowable modes: Auto - Internal algorithmic control of the system. Manual - External control of the system.
The reason the system is in the current operating state.

Turn system functionality on or off. The controls and communication are maintained, thus allowing the system to be turned on after being turned off.
iCOM Specific: The operation of the system is dependent upon this value and other conditions, such as an alarm state. The "off" command will always turn the system functionality off. For instance, this turns on/off all cooling, heating, humidifier, and dehumidifier functions.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription:
Fluid temperature measured at the inlet of the unit.
iCOM Specific Behavior: This value is used in determining activation of events evt_clng_tmpRetFluOver and evt_clng_tmpRetFluUnder. This is the fluid being returned TO this unit to be re-chilled.

Supply fluid temperature.
iCOM Specific Behavior: This value is used in determining activation of events evt_clng_tmpSupFluOver and evt_clng_tmpSupFluUnder. This is the fluid being supplied FROM this unit for cooling operations.

The actual set point value being used for the desired fluid temperature at the outlet of the unit.
iCOM Specific: This value is a function of val_clng_tmp_supFluSetPt1 and val_clng_tmp_supFluSetPt2. Its value may vary depending on time of day or other algorithmic parameters.
For water cooled condensers, the temperature of the water entering the heat exchanger, before cooling the refrigerant.
For water cooled condensers, the temperature of the water exiting the heat exchanger, after cooling the refrigerant.

Desired heated water temperature at the outlet of the unit.
iCOM Specific: This is the water being supplied FROM this unit for heating operations. It is only used on units with a heat pump feature.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Present free cooling utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum.
Present reheating utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum rated capacity.
Present compressor utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum rated capacity.

DataInt16.EngineeringDescription:
Air temperature as measured by external air sensor A.
iCOM Specific Behavior: This value is used in determining activation of event evt_ext_tmpAirOverA.

DataUint16.EngineeringDescription: Present compressor economizer utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum.
Present adiabatic cooling utilization expressed as a percentage of the maximum.

DataTime32.EngineeringDescription: The system date and time (generally based on a real-time clock). NOTE: This is generally the local time. It is not Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) unless the local time zone is GMT.
